				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">this kills our class... biggest nerf ever... </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Yeah, just like when they created auto-attack.  Curse them and their enjoyable gameplay ideas!
<br />

<br />
This has to be the biggest (only?) gameplay improvement ever given to bards.  I think this is like a breath of life, not the kiss of death.  If anyone thinks it's lazy, fine - then so is auto-attack, auto-run, any hotbutton or hotkey, or any other thing in the interface that lets you focus more on playing the game, interacting with others, and enjoying the MMORPG world.
<br />

<br />
I for one can't wait to actually chat with the group I'm in to some extent...at least more than three word bursts or sentences that break my twist while other caster buffs stay ticking merrily away on group members for minutes on end.
<br />

<br />
If people quit playing bards because of this, good riddance.  There will be plenty of new bards coming in to experience a class that has become more enjoyable to play.  It's not like twisting separates the good bards from the bad any more than smashing on the ranged attack button separates the good rangers from the bad.
<br />

