The stop on fizzle/missed note is a good thing. That should prevent an onslaught of bard bots until they invest in the required anti-fizzle AA. And without AE kiting that will take a while to build up to.
<br />

<br />
Most bard bots I know are macroquest or Nostromo powered anyhow. MQ/n52 bots are not stopped by fizzles anyhow. With a good script they keep right on twisting.
<br />

<br />
I'll stick to my manual 22334455, but its a nice option for others.
<br />

<br />
Good job Sony.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
