				<td colspan="2"><span>Everyone complaining about this take a deep breath, close your eyes and imagine this:
<br />

<br />
You're a programmer and you can't use your hands.  You get a sore throat from using voice recognition software to type documents.  You have difficulty washing your hair because your wrists hurt, in fact pretty much everything involving your hands is painful.
<br />

<br />
As someone who went through this in 2000, and believe me when I say this /melody function would have prevented it, all I have to say to the naysayers is try to be a little considerate of someone other than yourself.  It will make you a better person.
<br />

<br />
Also, if you think this somehow reduces the skill level required to play a bard, you're playing the wrong game.  Go play Doom 3.</span></td>
