			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've always thought it was inconsistent that Sony would be anti-macro in EQ but would launch SWG with fully supported editable macros...
<br />

<br />
I played SWG a bit and never really used the macro feature because I actually had some fun using the interface as intended. Setting up the macro and afk'ing while skilling up, while done by many players there, just seemed to defeat the purpose of playing the game to &quot;play a game.&quot;
<br />

<br />
With the exception of the increase in fizzle which appeared suspiciously close to the release of the AA to reduce fizzle (CONSPIRACY!) I've always liked twisting. The increase to fizzle is an annoyance but twisting is still organic game play to me.
<br />

<br />
I like that &quot;twisting&quot; requires the ability to multi-task and to be at least partially conscious. 
<br />

<br />
I'm cool with them patching in a macro for people with carpal tunnel issues. I probably won't use it just like I didn't use the SWG macros and didn't ever AoE kite for l337 exp... it's a valid addition to the game for a lot of CT-afflicted people and if it gets exploited I won't care any more than I did that 8 bards in all of EQ were consistently AE 'sploiting for mad aa's.
<br />

<br />
In my day we ate deaths, mashed 11,22,33, till our wrists were blue, ran from HHK to Qeynos without selo and WE LIKED IT!!! 
<br />

<br />
Aminna</span></td>
